  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      .The aim of this study is to identify the analgesic effect of intraoperative ketamine
      intravenous infusion on patients undergoing intestinal surgery and its effect on salivary
      cortisol and alpha amylase levels as indicator of its effect.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      I- Group K (ketamine): 30 patients will receive intraoperative intravenous ketamine infusion.

      II- Group C (control): 30 patients will receive intraoperative intravenous normal saline
      infusion.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
